THIS: -> >>4519218
For anyone not aware of it, the photographer watched the marines raise the American flag, but missed the shot. I don't recall why, but he recognized how powerful that moment was. So he had some marines re-stage it the next day when he had his good cameras on hand to "spontaneously catch the moment."

There were some other details, like the marines in this shot are all dressed up immaculately, whereas the day before the marines who raised the first flag were dressed as they had come off the battlefield, a complete mess. Not certain if I remember this correctly, but the weather the day before may also have not been very good, also compromising the aesthetics of the shot.

There are pictures of the first flag being raised, I've seen a couple of them. They were marginal quality (weather, camera, dunno) and the digital copies I saw posted were fairly low resolution. Not sure if they could even qualify for /hr/.

Anyway, zoom in and study how these guys are dressed and posed. It's a pretty immaculate composition, but not a spontaneous capture of the real moment.
